	In problems 5#, do the following:

	> a) Find the eigenvalues of $A$.

	> b) Find the corresponding eigenvectors and generalized eigenvectors of $A$.

	> c) Determine if $A$ is diagonalizable. If it is, write $A = BDB^{-1}$ for a diagonal matrix $D$, and if not, write $A = BJB^{-1}$ for a matrix $J$ in Jordan normal form (you don't need to invert $B$).

	> d) If $A$ is diagonalizable, determine if there is an orthonormal basis of eigenvectors; if so, find it.

	> e) If the eigenvalues of $A$ are distinct, find the general solution to the system of differential equations $\vec{x}' = A\vec{x}$.

	#. $A = [[ 3, 1 ; -1, 1 ]]$.

	#. $A = [[ 2, 1, 0 ; 0, 1, 0 ; 1, -1, 3 ]]$.

	#. $A = [[ -3, -1, -3 ; -8, -3, -8 ; 4, 1, 3 ]]$.

	#. $A = [[ -9, -10, -10 ; 4, 4, 3 ; 1, 2, 3 ]]$.

	#. $A = [[ 1, 3, 0, 0 ; 3, 1, 0, 0 ; 0, 0, 1, -3 ; 0, 0, -3, 1 ]]$.

