	In problems 3#, do the following:

	> a) Find a singular value decomposition $A = U \Sigma V^T$.

	> b) Find a least-squares solution to $A\vec{x} = \vec{b}$.

	> c) Determine if the least-squares solution is unique.

	#. $A = [[ 1, 2 ; 2, 1 ; 1, 1 ]]$ and $\vec{b} = [[ 1 ; 2 ; 2 ]]$.

	#. $A = [[ 3, 1, 4 ; 2, 0, 1 ]]$ and $\vec{b} = [[ 1 ; -2 ]]$.

	#. $A = [[ 1, -1, 0 ; 1, 0, 1 ; 2, -1, 1 ]]$ and $\vec{b} = [[ 1 ; 2 ; -1 ]]$.

